"n. 天蓝色；adj. 蔚蓝的 【英】 adj. 蔚蓝的(sky blue) adj. 蔚蓝的; n 天蓝色 【例】an azure sky 碧蓝的天空 【记】a一个, zure拼: 足热. 一个足够热的天气. 一定是阳光暴晒, 万里无云, 所以天是蔚蓝的. 【记】ozone 臭氧层，使得天变得azure 蓝 azure (n.)  early 14c., from Old French azur, asur, a color name, from a false separation of Arabic (al)-lazaward ""lapis lazuli,"" as though the -l- were the French article l'. The Arabic name is from Persian lajward, from Lajward, a place in Turkestan, mentioned by Marco Polo, where the stone was collected."
